column4: Grundon Waste Management Conditional Jockeys' Novices' Handicap Hurdle (GBB Race)
column20: 11/4 At The Oche, 11/2 Akimos, 6/1 Byzantium,  Theatre Of Flight, 7/1 Graham, 8/1 Mount Anglesby,  Sage Green, 12/1 John Barbour, 16/1 Thistle Be The One
column36: Got his act together in Ffos Las maiden in April; can improve again in handicaps
column37: Made shaky start to hurdling career but got his act together at third attempt, staying on well to win Ffos Las maiden (2m3f, soft) in April; could easily have more to offer in handicaps this season and enters calculations.

column4: Grundon Waste Management Conditional Jockeys' Novices' Handicap Hurdle (GBB Race)
column20: 11/4 At The Oche, 11/2 Akimos, 6/1 Byzantium,  Theatre Of Flight, 7/1 Graham, 8/1 Mount Anglesby,  Sage Green, 12/1 John Barbour, 16/1 Thistle Be The One
column36: Second in valuable series final at Worcester in September; can make presence felt again
column37: 2-3 in points in early part of this year and returned from break with two good efforts under rules, latterly when second (albeit well held) in valuable series final at Worcester (2m4f, good) in September; can make presence felt again here.

column4: Grundon Waste Management Conditional Jockeys' Novices' Handicap Hurdle (GBB Race)
column20: 11/4 At The Oche, 11/2 Akimos, 6/1 Byzantium,  Theatre Of Flight, 7/1 Graham, 8/1 Mount Anglesby,  Sage Green, 12/1 John Barbour, 16/1 Thistle Be The One
column36: Struck form with two wins in June (handicap/novice); tendency to race too freely a worry
column37: Came good with comfortable handicap win at Warwick (2m3f, good) in June, his seventh hurdling start, and easily followed up in modest novice event at Newton Abbot (2m5f, good) later that month; further progress is possible but his tendency to race too freely remains a nagging concern.

column4: Grundon Waste Management Conditional Jockeys' Novices' Handicap Hurdle (GBB Race)
column20: 11/4 At The Oche, 11/2 Akimos, 6/1 Byzantium,  Theatre Of Flight, 7/1 Graham, 8/1 Mount Anglesby,  Sage Green, 12/1 John Barbour, 16/1 Thistle Be The One
column36: Disappointing odds-on favourite on seasonal debut but may still have potential
column37: Disappointing odds-on favourite when well-held fourth on last month's seasonal debut at Newton Abbot but looked promising as a novice hurdler last season and may still have potential.

column4: Grundon Waste Management Conditional Jockeys' Novices' Handicap Hurdle (GBB Race)
column20: 11/4 At The Oche, 11/2 Akimos, 6/1 Byzantium,  Theatre Of Flight, 7/1 Graham, 8/1 Mount Anglesby,  Sage Green, 12/1 John Barbour, 16/1 Thistle Be The One
column36: Made good start to hurdle career over 2m at end of last season; this longer trip will suit
column37: Irish point winner; left disappointing bumper debut behind when causing 40-1 surprise on hurdle debut for Anthony Charlton at Warwick (2m, good; first-time hood) in March and subsequent Chepstow second (2m, good) was perfectly respectable; likely to be suited by the step up on trip for this seasonal/stable/handicap debut; must be considered.

column4: Grundon Waste Management Conditional Jockeys' Novices' Handicap Hurdle (GBB Race)
column20: 11/4 At The Oche, 11/2 Akimos, 6/1 Byzantium,  Theatre Of Flight, 7/1 Graham, 8/1 Mount Anglesby,  Sage Green, 12/1 John Barbour, 16/1 Thistle Be The One
column36: Safely held last month but won readily on stable debut in September; back in trip here
column37: Safely held when fifth at Chepstow three weeks ago but justified heavy market support on stable debut at Worcester (2m7f, good) in September, winning readily by over 5l, and could still build on that performance if coping with today's drop back in trip.

column4: Grundon Waste Management Conditional Jockeys' Novices' Handicap Hurdle (GBB Race)
column20: 11/4 At The Oche, 11/2 Akimos, 6/1 Byzantium,  Theatre Of Flight, 7/1 Graham, 8/1 Mount Anglesby,  Sage Green, 12/1 John Barbour, 16/1 Thistle Be The One

column4: Grundon Waste Management Conditional Jockeys' Novices' Handicap Hurdle (GBB Race)
column20: 11/4 At The Oche, 11/2 Akimos, 6/1 Byzantium,  Theatre Of Flight, 7/1 Graham, 8/1 Mount Anglesby,  Sage Green, 12/1 John Barbour, 16/1 Thistle Be The One
column36: 0-7 over hurdles but ran well in defeat on last two outings (2m4f/1m7f); in the mix again
column37: 0-7 over hurdles but went very close at Down Royal (2m4f good to firm) in August and also ran well when second at Roscommon (1m7f, good to yielding) in September; probably won't be far away.

column4: Grundon Waste Management Conditional Jockeys' Novices' Handicap Hurdle (GBB Race)
column20: 11/4 At The Oche, 11/2 Akimos, 6/1 Byzantium,  Theatre Of Flight, 7/1 Graham, 8/1 Mount Anglesby,  Sage Green, 12/1 John Barbour, 16/1 Thistle Be The One
column36: Made heavy weather of landing 1-5 odds last month but remains unexposed; major player
column37: Made quite heavy weather of winning Ffos Las maiden (2m, good) at 1-5 odds last month but remains very unexposed over hurdles after only two attempts and the form of his clear second at Newton Abbot in September was very well advertised by the winner last weekend.

column4: Grundon Waste Management Conditional Jockeys' Novices' Handicap Hurdle (GBB Race)
column20: 11/4 At The Oche, 11/2 Akimos, 6/1 Byzantium,  Theatre Of Flight, 7/1 Graham, 8/1 Mount Anglesby,  Sage Green, 12/1 John Barbour, 16/1 Thistle Be The One
column36: 0-7 over hurdles; can probably win soon but is up in grade here; others appeal more
column37: Unseated rider mid-race when well backed for Fontwell handicap six weeks ago and now 0-7 over hurdles; not one to give up on just yet but moves up in grade today and others in this line-up may have more potential.

column4: Ascot Underwriting Novices' Limited Handicap Chase (GBB Race)
column20: 9/4 No Questions Asked, 3/1 Viroflay, 4/1 Lylian, 9/2 Old Gregorian, 5/1 Don't Tell Su
column36: Smart hunter chaser; 2m2f looks short but he's a front-runner who doesn't hang about
column37: Suited by a sound surface; won a juvenile hurdle for this yard in 2020 before embarking on a point/hunter chase career that by and large went very well, and last time ran to a high level when second to the classy Its On The Line in a 3m hunter chase at Punchestown; a long time since he ran over this short a trip but he's a front-runner who doesn't hang about; Olive Nicholls knows him well.

column4: Ascot Underwriting Novices' Limited Handicap Chase (GBB Race)
column20: 9/4 No Questions Asked, 3/1 Viroflay, 4/1 Lylian, 9/2 Old Gregorian, 5/1 Don't Tell Su

column4: Ascot Underwriting Novices' Limited Handicap Chase (GBB Race)
column20: 9/4 No Questions Asked, 3/1 Viroflay, 4/1 Lylian, 9/2 Old Gregorian, 5/1 Don't Tell Su
column36: Progressive hurdler; jumped well in the main when finishing alone on chase debut
column37: Nicely progressive over hurdles last season and finished third in the valuable Morebattle at Kelso (2m, good to soft) in March off only 2lb lower; gifted his first race over fences at Wetherby (2m3f, good) when his sole rival unseated but this 6yo jumped well in the main; respected.

column4: Ascot Underwriting Novices' Limited Handicap Chase (GBB Race)
column20: 9/4 No Questions Asked, 3/1 Viroflay, 4/1 Lylian, 9/2 Old Gregorian, 5/1 Don't Tell Su
column36: Failed to fire on chase debut (last run) but on a competitive mark; changed yards
column37: Failed to fire on chase debut at Sandown in March on what proved to be his final run for Paul Nicholls (remains with same owners); only 1-8 as a hurdler but was runner-up five times and on peak form he's on a competitive mark; a bit of rain wouldn't go amiss.

column4: Ascot Underwriting Novices' Limited Handicap Chase (GBB Race)
column20: 9/4 No Questions Asked, 3/1 Viroflay, 4/1 Lylian, 9/2 Old Gregorian, 5/1 Don't Tell Su
column32: T Jacobs And Mrs E Avery
column36: The stable has won this with a 4yo before and he won over fences in France in June
column37: The stable has won this with a 4yo (Nassalam) before and he won one of his two chase starts in France earlier this year (2m6f, soft); goodish ground will be a first but that might be no hindrance judged on comments made in this week's Racing Post Stable Tour; dangerously unexposed.

column4: Grundon Waste Management Handicap Chase (Premier Handicap) (GBB Race)
column20: 3/1 L'Eau du Sud, 6/1 Martator, 13/2 Boothill, 8/1 Issar d'Airy, 9/1 Special Cadeau,  General Medrano, 10/1 Sans Bruit, 12/1 Petit Tonnerre,  Teddy Blue, 16/1 Western General,  Shakeyatailfeather, 25/1 Authorized Art,  Gabriel's Getaway
column36: Classy on his day but prone to mistakes; even if in tune he has to carry 12st
column37: Won this two years ago on soft and followed up on his return visit (same month) when the ground was good; a couple of runs behind Jonbon read well but he has mistakes in him and hit the deck in three of his subsequent six starts; even if in tune this afternoon he faces no easy task with 12st.

column4: Grundon Waste Management Handicap Chase (Premier Handicap) (GBB Race)
column20: 3/1 L'Eau du Sud, 6/1 Martator, 13/2 Boothill, 8/1 Issar d'Airy, 9/1 Special Cadeau,  General Medrano, 10/1 Sans Bruit, 12/1 Petit Tonnerre,  Teddy Blue, 16/1 Western General,  Shakeyatailfeather, 25/1 Authorized Art,  Gabriel's Getaway
column27: E A R L Du Moulin
column32: Mason, Hogarth, Ferguson, Hales, The Late J Hales
column36: One of Britain's best 2m novice chasers last season; high in the weights for a reason
column37: One of Britain's best 2m novice chasers last season and held his own in the Grade 1s at Cheltenham and Aintree; didn't jump as well as he can on the latter occasion when tried in cheekpieces and those aids are now left off; high in the weights for a reason but he may prefer softer ground and will have new handling, having only been ridden by Harry Skelton in Britain.

column4: Grundon Waste Management Handicap Chase (Premier Handicap) (GBB Race)
column20: 3/1 L'Eau du Sud, 6/1 Martator, 13/2 Boothill, 8/1 Issar d'Airy, 9/1 Special Cadeau,  General Medrano, 10/1 Sans Bruit, 12/1 Petit Tonnerre,  Teddy Blue, 16/1 Western General,  Shakeyatailfeather, 25/1 Authorized Art,  Gabriel's Getaway
column36: Smart front-running two-miler on his day but does tend to come good in the spring
column37: Up with the pace throughout when winning valuable handicaps in the spring at Aintree (good to soft) and Plumpton (good), latterly in the hands of Jay Tidball; raised a collective 14lb for those and he does tend to come good in the spring.

column4: Grundon Waste Management Handicap Chase (Premier Handicap) (GBB Race)
column20: 3/1 L'Eau du Sud, 6/1 Martator, 13/2 Boothill, 8/1 Issar d'Airy, 9/1 Special Cadeau,  General Medrano, 10/1 Sans Bruit, 12/1 Petit Tonnerre,  Teddy Blue, 16/1 Western General,  Shakeyatailfeather, 25/1 Authorized Art,  Gabriel's Getaway
column27: M H Sly, Dr T Davies & Mrs P Sly
column36: Commendable effort at the weights when runner-up in a Grade 3 novice at Roscommon
column37: Already a better chaser than hurdler and it was a commendable effort at the weights when runner-up in a Grade 3 novice at Roscommon a month ago (2m, good to yielding); has scope for further progress and in-form Irish stable always respected on British forays.

column4: Grundon Waste Management Handicap Chase (Premier Handicap) (GBB Race)
column20: 3/1 L'Eau du Sud, 6/1 Martator, 13/2 Boothill, 8/1 Issar d'Airy, 9/1 Special Cadeau,  General Medrano, 10/1 Sans Bruit, 12/1 Petit Tonnerre,  Teddy Blue, 16/1 Western General,  Shakeyatailfeather, 25/1 Authorized Art,  Gabriel's Getaway
column36: Won this last year and 3-4 at Ascot; dangerously handicapped again; major player
column37: Won his final three races of the 2023/24 season and hit the ground running last campaign with back-to-back wins over C&D, including this race (on good; enhancing fine course record); his subsequent loss of form has been a blessing mark-wise and he's a massive danger to all if he can return to action with his revs up; stable quiet but that was also the case this time last year.

column4: Grundon Waste Management Handicap Chase (Premier Handicap) (GBB Race)
column20: 3/1 L'Eau du Sud, 6/1 Martator, 13/2 Boothill, 8/1 Issar d'Airy, 9/1 Special Cadeau,  General Medrano, 10/1 Sans Bruit, 12/1 Petit Tonnerre,  Teddy Blue, 16/1 Western General,  Shakeyatailfeather, 25/1 Authorized Art,  Gabriel's Getaway
column36: This mark isn't beyond him and he returns with his stable ticking along very nicely
column37: Very well in with Petit Tonnerre on their Doncaster clash in January, after which he ran okay in the Grand Annual before a disappointing run at Aintree; this mark isn't beyond him and he returns with his stable ticking along very nicely.

column4: Grundon Waste Management Handicap Chase (Premier Handicap) (GBB Race)
column20: 3/1 L'Eau du Sud, 6/1 Martator, 13/2 Boothill, 8/1 Issar d'Airy, 9/1 Special Cadeau,  General Medrano, 10/1 Sans Bruit, 12/1 Petit Tonnerre,  Teddy Blue, 16/1 Western General,  Shakeyatailfeather, 25/1 Authorized Art,  Gabriel's Getaway
column36: He has got himself high in the weights and has been plying his trade at a lower level
column37: Won three handicaps last season at about 2m on heavy, soft and good ground; latest run was too bad to be true but he has got himself high in the weights and has been plying his trade at a lower level; this looks challenging.

column4: Grundon Waste Management Handicap Chase (Premier Handicap) (GBB Race)
column20: 3/1 L'Eau du Sud, 6/1 Martator, 13/2 Boothill, 8/1 Issar d'Airy, 9/1 Special Cadeau,  General Medrano, 10/1 Sans Bruit, 12/1 Petit Tonnerre,  Teddy Blue, 16/1 Western General,  Shakeyatailfeather, 25/1 Authorized Art,  Gabriel's Getaway
column27: A De La Motte Saint Pierre Et Al
column36: Career-best form in winning a huge-field Punchestown handicap back in the spring
column37: Hasn't been the easiest to predict over fences but it all came together in a big way when coming clear in a huge-field 2m handicap at the Punchestown festival back in the spring (yielding); has run well after a break and could feature if he's got out of bed on the right side.

column4: Grundon Waste Management Handicap Chase (Premier Handicap) (GBB Race)
column20: 3/1 L'Eau du Sud, 6/1 Martator, 13/2 Boothill, 8/1 Issar d'Airy, 9/1 Special Cadeau,  General Medrano, 10/1 Sans Bruit, 12/1 Petit Tonnerre,  Teddy Blue, 16/1 Western General,  Shakeyatailfeather, 25/1 Authorized Art,  Gabriel's Getaway
column36: A 10yo now and needed to run a lot better than he did at Kempton two weeks ago
column37: Flashes of smart form for Willie Mullins but a 10yo now and hasn't yet threatened a breakthrough win for the Moores; needed to run a lot better than he did at Kempton two weeks ago.

column4: Grundon Waste Management Handicap Chase (Premier Handicap) (GBB Race)
column20: 3/1 L'Eau du Sud, 6/1 Martator, 13/2 Boothill, 8/1 Issar d'Airy, 9/1 Special Cadeau,  General Medrano, 10/1 Sans Bruit, 12/1 Petit Tonnerre,  Teddy Blue, 16/1 Western General,  Shakeyatailfeather, 25/1 Authorized Art,  Gabriel's Getaway
column36: 2-5 over fences but debatable whether he's quite up to winning a handicap of this stature
column37: Useful hurdler, if not that reliable; won two of his five chases last season and off the same mark here as when running well in his bid for a hat-trick at Newbury (2m, good); debatable whether he's quite up to winning a handicap of this stature.

column4: Grundon Waste Management Handicap Chase (Premier Handicap) (GBB Race)
column20: 3/1 L'Eau du Sud, 6/1 Martator, 13/2 Boothill, 8/1 Issar d'Airy, 9/1 Special Cadeau,  General Medrano, 10/1 Sans Bruit, 12/1 Petit Tonnerre,  Teddy Blue, 16/1 Western General,  Shakeyatailfeather, 25/1 Authorized Art,  Gabriel's Getaway
column36: Recent Kelso winner; this is tougher again and has only won on left-handed tracks
column37: Perhaps had a fitness edge when beating two reliable yardsticks at Kelso (2m1f, good) and that triggered an 8lb rise in the weights (also 1lb out of the handicap here); this race demands another personal best and all her wins have come on left-handed tracks.

column4: Grundon Waste Management Handicap Chase (Premier Handicap) (GBB Race)
column20: 3/1 L'Eau du Sud, 6/1 Martator, 13/2 Boothill, 8/1 Issar d'Airy, 9/1 Special Cadeau,  General Medrano, 10/1 Sans Bruit, 12/1 Petit Tonnerre,  Teddy Blue, 16/1 Western General,  Shakeyatailfeather, 25/1 Authorized Art,  Gabriel's Getaway
column27: S C E A De La Vallee De L'Orne &c Yves
column36: Quite well in on flashes of form, including his second in this last year; able when fresh
column37: Favourably treated with Martator on his beating of that rival in late 2023 and, when second to the Williams horse in this last year, he committed a good way from home; didn't really fire back in the spring but he's very able when fresh and worth a second look despite being 2lb wrong; Freddie Mitchell aboard for five of his last six races.

column4: Grundon Waste Management Handicap Chase (Premier Handicap) (GBB Race)
column20: 3/1 L'Eau du Sud, 6/1 Martator, 13/2 Boothill, 8/1 Issar d'Airy, 9/1 Special Cadeau,  General Medrano, 10/1 Sans Bruit, 12/1 Petit Tonnerre,  Teddy Blue, 16/1 Western General,  Shakeyatailfeather, 25/1 Authorized Art,  Gabriel's Getaway
column36: Fair return at Kempton but in a lot deeper here and especially from 7lb out of the weights
column37: Strike-rate of 4-9 over fences; pulled up in Petit Tonnerre's race at Punchestown in May but made a pleasing return from wind surgery to finish second at Kempton recently; however, in a lot deeper here and especially from 7lb out of the weights.

column4: Gl Events Novices' Hurdle (GBB Race)
column20: 6/4 Soomaroy, 11/4 Military Alliance, 3/1 Trustintimes, 8/1 Start Again, 9/1 Ice In The Veins, 33/1 Directly, 100/1 Gower Spirit
column32: The Time On Our Hands Boys' Syndicate
column36: Won bumper at Kempton and two hurdle races at Uttoxeter; can do better still; gives weight
column37: Won a bumper at Kempton in March, did just enough on hurdling debut at Uttoxeter in May and asserted on run-in from his only market rival when back at Uttoxeter (again 2m on good) in June; that puts him on a four-timer (and means he gives weight all round today) and he can do better still.

column4: Gl Events Novices' Hurdle (GBB Race)
column20: 6/4 Soomaroy, 11/4 Military Alliance, 3/1 Trustintimes, 8/1 Start Again, 9/1 Ice In The Veins, 33/1 Directly, 100/1 Gower Spirit
column36: Won by a neck for new yard in maiden at Hereford (2m, good) in April; brings potential
column37: His four-race Irish career stalled but he made a winning start for new yard by a neck in maiden hurdle at Hereford (2m, good) in April, leading at the final flight; the second, third, sixth and ninth have won over hurdles since; with more still to learn in that Hereford race, he brings potential as well as a leading chance on form.

column4: Gl Events Novices' Hurdle (GBB Race)
column20: 6/4 Soomaroy, 11/4 Military Alliance, 3/1 Trustintimes, 8/1 Start Again, 9/1 Ice In The Veins, 33/1 Directly, 100/1 Gower Spirit

column4: Gl Events Novices' Hurdle (GBB Race)
column20: 6/4 Soomaroy, 11/4 Military Alliance, 3/1 Trustintimes, 8/1 Start Again, 9/1 Ice In The Veins, 33/1 Directly, 100/1 Gower Spirit
column36: Showed a bit of ability in bumper and novice hurdle but others have much more solid claims
column37: Showed a bit of ability in a Worcester bumper (good) and Leicester novice (1m7f, heavy; beaten 21l) but others have much more solid claims.

column4: Gl Events Novices' Hurdle (GBB Race)
column20: 6/4 Soomaroy, 11/4 Military Alliance, 3/1 Trustintimes, 8/1 Start Again, 9/1 Ice In The Veins, 33/1 Directly, 100/1 Gower Spirit
column36: Player on his bumper form but opposable judged on his two odds-on defeats as a hurdler
column37: Second and first (Worcester) in his two bumpers; he did not live up to that when second at 4-11 in maiden hurdle at Warwick (2m, good) in June, when mistakes did not help, and that was better than his hard-pulling fourth when 8-13 at Worcester (2m4f) five weeks ago; a hood is enlisted; player on the bumper form but opposable on hurdling evidence.

column4: Gl Events Novices' Hurdle (GBB Race)
column20: 6/4 Soomaroy, 11/4 Military Alliance, 3/1 Trustintimes, 8/1 Start Again, 9/1 Ice In The Veins, 33/1 Directly, 100/1 Gower Spirit
column27: S C E A Le Haras D'Haspel
column36: 4l winner of an Irish maiden point (3m, good to yielding) in March; £190,000 buy in April
column37: 42,000euros 3yo; second foal; half-brother to a French 1m3f/1m4f winner; dam French 1m2f winner, half-sister to French 5.5f-1m Flat and prolific 2m1f-2m6f hurdle/chase winner The Stomp; joint-favourite when 4l winner of an Irish maiden point (3m, good to yielding) in March; fetched £190,000 in April and very much one to note for trainer with fine record in this race.

column4: Gl Events Novices' Hurdle (GBB Race)
column20: 6/4 Soomaroy, 11/4 Military Alliance, 3/1 Trustintimes, 8/1 Start Again, 9/1 Ice In The Veins, 33/1 Directly, 100/1 Gower Spirit

column4: Lavazza Handicap Hurdle (GBB Race)
column20: 7/2 Alexei, 5/1 Washington, 6/1 Indemnity,  Dance And Glance, 8/1 Ooh Betty,  Moveit Like Minnie, 10/1 Fasol, 12/1 Afadil, 14/1 High Fibre, 16/1 Torrent, 25/1 No Ordinary Joe, 33/1 Maasai Mara
column36: Became inconsistent for Nicky Henderson and did not show enough on debut for new yard
column37: Player on best form for Nicky Henderson but inconsistent and did not show enough on debut for new connections 15 days ago.

column4: Lavazza Handicap Hurdle (GBB Race)
column20: 7/2 Alexei, 5/1 Washington, 6/1 Indemnity,  Dance And Glance, 8/1 Ooh Betty,  Moveit Like Minnie, 10/1 Fasol, 12/1 Afadil, 14/1 High Fibre, 16/1 Torrent, 25/1 No Ordinary Joe, 33/1 Maasai Mara
column36: Won last November after a similar break and second wind surgery; has now had her third
column37: Can make the running; raised her game with best efforts last term, one over C&D and also a close third in the Scottish Champion Hurdle at Ayr in April (1lb higher today); flopped in May when last seen and has since had her third wind operation; probably needs to resume progress but she did win last November after a similar break and second wind surgery.

column4: Lavazza Handicap Hurdle (GBB Race)
column20: 7/2 Alexei, 5/1 Washington, 6/1 Indemnity,  Dance And Glance, 8/1 Ooh Betty,  Moveit Like Minnie, 10/1 Fasol, 12/1 Afadil, 14/1 High Fibre, 16/1 Torrent, 25/1 No Ordinary Joe, 33/1 Maasai Mara
column36: 2m win from Moveit Like Minnie at Chepstow when miles clear of the other four; shortlisted
column37: Won at Chepstow last October and followed up in a valuable handicap in Ireland; struggled afterwards last season but returned three weeks ago with a win from Moveit Like Minnie in the same Chepstow race (2m, good) when they finished miles clear of the other four; back up 4lb; shortlisted.

column4: Lavazza Handicap Hurdle (GBB Race)
column20: 7/2 Alexei, 5/1 Washington, 6/1 Indemnity,  Dance And Glance, 8/1 Ooh Betty,  Moveit Like Minnie, 10/1 Fasol, 12/1 Afadil, 14/1 High Fibre, 16/1 Torrent, 25/1 No Ordinary Joe, 33/1 Maasai Mara
column36: Returned with good 2nd off this mark in useful race at Chepstow (2m, good) three weeks ago
column37: German Flat winner who had two comfortable novice wins at Taunton (2m3f/2m) towards the end of last year; raced too freely on handicap hurdle debut in March (2m3f) but returned with a good second off this mark in useful race at Chepstow (2m, good) three weeks ago; needs a second look.

column4: Lavazza Handicap Hurdle (GBB Race)
column20: 7/2 Alexei, 5/1 Washington, 6/1 Indemnity,  Dance And Glance, 8/1 Ooh Betty,  Moveit Like Minnie, 10/1 Fasol, 12/1 Afadil, 14/1 High Fibre, 16/1 Torrent, 25/1 No Ordinary Joe, 33/1 Maasai Mara
column36: Right out of form on last two outings; had a wind operation (his third) in July
column37: 12l fourth in this race on last autumn's second run; placed in two good handicaps in February/March but right out of form in his last two outings; plenty seems to depend on the wind operation (his third) he had in July.

column4: Lavazza Handicap Hurdle (GBB Race)
column20: 7/2 Alexei, 5/1 Washington, 6/1 Indemnity,  Dance And Glance, 8/1 Ooh Betty,  Moveit Like Minnie, 10/1 Fasol, 12/1 Afadil, 14/1 High Fibre, 16/1 Torrent, 25/1 No Ordinary Joe, 33/1 Maasai Mara
column36: 3-3 in handicap hurdles; up another 6lb but keeps looking as if he has more up his sleeve
column37: Pretty useful in 2024 on Flat; won on good ground at Huntingdon, Warwick and Market Rasen (2m1f) in all three of his handicap hurdles, with mistakes at the last two flights on latest outing but he'd travelled much the best and won by nearly 2l; up another 6lb and in class but he keeps looking as if he has more up his sleeve.

column4: Lavazza Handicap Hurdle (GBB Race)
column20: 7/2 Alexei, 5/1 Washington, 6/1 Indemnity,  Dance And Glance, 8/1 Ooh Betty,  Moveit Like Minnie, 10/1 Fasol, 12/1 Afadil, 14/1 High Fibre, 16/1 Torrent, 25/1 No Ordinary Joe, 33/1 Maasai Mara
column27: Aston Mullins Stud & S Barrow Esq
column36: 22-1 for handicap at Chepstow (2m, good) on return but put up a bold show to be second
column37: Won twice last summer and third in three Grade 2 events in the winter; 22-1 for handicap at Chepstow (2m, good) three weeks ago but put up a bold show to be second of 13; back up 2lb but that was a positive return to action.

column4: Lavazza Handicap Hurdle (GBB Race)
column20: 7/2 Alexei, 5/1 Washington, 6/1 Indemnity,  Dance And Glance, 8/1 Ooh Betty,  Moveit Like Minnie, 10/1 Fasol, 12/1 Afadil, 14/1 High Fibre, 16/1 Torrent, 25/1 No Ordinary Joe, 33/1 Maasai Mara
column32: F J Mills & W R Mills
column36: Consistent in last five hurdle races, three here; second to Washington at Chepstow latest
column37: Comes with risks over fences but consistent in his last five hurdle races, the first three of which were at this track; second to Washington at Chepstow (2m, good) three weeks ago; needs to find a bit extra and has a headgear change today, plus 5lb claimer on board.

column4: Lavazza Handicap Hurdle (GBB Race)
column20: 7/2 Alexei, 5/1 Washington, 6/1 Indemnity,  Dance And Glance, 8/1 Ooh Betty,  Moveit Like Minnie, 10/1 Fasol, 12/1 Afadil, 14/1 High Fibre, 16/1 Torrent, 25/1 No Ordinary Joe, 33/1 Maasai Mara
column36: Second in two of his three handicaps, with fifth of 16 in a hot race in between
column37: Maiden and novice winner who was second in two of his three handicaps, with fifth of 16 in a hot race in between; probably just held when he blundered two out at Newton Abbot (2m1f, good to soft) two weeks ago but that was his first run for five months and he may be able to build on it.

column4: Lavazza Handicap Hurdle (GBB Race)
column20: 7/2 Alexei, 5/1 Washington, 6/1 Indemnity,  Dance And Glance, 8/1 Ooh Betty,  Moveit Like Minnie, 10/1 Fasol, 12/1 Afadil, 14/1 High Fibre, 16/1 Torrent, 25/1 No Ordinary Joe, 33/1 Maasai Mara
column32: P J Vogt And Bryan Drew
column36: 1-10 hurdling; 3rd in hot handicap in April; below-form favourite for a novice 3 weeks ago
column37: Smart at his peak on Flat (2023) but sole win from ten hurdle races was a maiden at Taunton (2m, good) in March; third in a hot handicap at Sandown (2m, good) in April but not so good when favourite for a Chepstow novice three weeks ago and he does not seem the percentage call.

column4: Lavazza Handicap Hurdle (GBB Race)
column20: 7/2 Alexei, 5/1 Washington, 6/1 Indemnity,  Dance And Glance, 8/1 Ooh Betty,  Moveit Like Minnie, 10/1 Fasol, 12/1 Afadil, 14/1 High Fibre, 16/1 Torrent, 25/1 No Ordinary Joe, 33/1 Maasai Mara
column32: G C Stevens And Mrs C Fry
column36: Reliable over hurdles until a modest latest show; needs a new high in first-time headgear

column20: 5/2 Envoi Allen, 11/4 Western Fold, 3/1 Spillane's Tower, 9/2 Found A Fifty, 12/1 Affordale Fury, 14/1 Stellar Story, 100/1 Flash Collonges
column27: G A E C Delorme Freres
column36: Useful sort for Paul Nicholls early in his career; completely out of his depth here
column37: Useful sort for Paul Nicholls early in his career; last win was March 2023; tailed off in a Downpatrick handicap hurdle in July on stable debut and has missed all three engagements since; completely out of his depth here.

column4: BetVictor Champion Chase (Grade 1)
column20: 5/2 Envoi Allen, 11/4 Western Fold, 3/1 Spillane's Tower, 9/2 Found A Fifty, 12/1 Affordale Fury, 14/1 Stellar Story, 100/1 Flash Collonges
column36: High-class at 2m4f, major chance of staying this longer trip
column37: High-class novice, winning 2m Grade 1 Aintree contest, and reappeared at this meeting last year to win 2m4f Grade 2 event before following up in 2m Grade 2 Fortria at Navan; back to 2m4f for career-best on final start of season when landing Grade 2 Fairyhouse contest at Easter, idling late on in testing conditions; first attempt at 3m and major player if staying.

column4: BetVictor Champion Chase (Grade 1)
column20: 5/2 Envoi Allen, 11/4 Western Fold, 3/1 Spillane's Tower, 9/2 Found A Fifty, 12/1 Affordale Fury, 14/1 Stellar Story, 100/1 Flash Collonges
column36: Comeback run last season was a career-best so has to be respected here on return
column37: Completed Grade 1 double at Fairyhouse (2m4f) and Punchestown (3m1f) as a novice and reappeared last autumn with career-best second to Fact Or File in 2m4f John Durkan at latter venue; both subsequent efforts at 3m were a bit underwhelming, ground possibly on the quick side in King George and in Punchestown Gold Cup blundered four out when a remote second to Galopin Des Champs; goes well fresh so has to be respected on overall form.

column4: BetVictor Champion Chase (Grade 1)
column20: 5/2 Envoi Allen, 11/4 Western Fold, 3/1 Spillane's Tower, 9/2 Found A Fifty, 12/1 Affordale Fury, 14/1 Stellar Story, 100/1 Flash Collonges
column36: Smart novice last season but stiff ask on seasonal return; would like softer ground too
column37: Won Albert Bartlett Novice Hurdle season before last; similarly high standard level of form in last season's novice chase campaign, notably narrow defeat in 3m Grade 2 Navan nov and second in a steadily run 3m1f Brown Advisory at Cheltenham; season finale at Punchestown was below best; ideally wants it softer.

column4: BetVictor Champion Chase (Grade 1)
column20: 5/2 Envoi Allen, 11/4 Western Fold, 3/1 Spillane's Tower, 9/2 Found A Fifty, 12/1 Affordale Fury, 14/1 Stellar Story, 100/1 Flash Collonges
column36: Tremendously progressive 6yo novice a danger to all if ground doesn't become too soft
column37: Tremendously progressive 6yo novice comes here seeking a five-timer, notably impressive 2m6f Galway Plate success and (after 66-day break) when beating Affordale Fury with plenty to spare in 2m4f Grade 2 PWC Champion Chase at Gowran last month on ground considered plenty soft (yielding-to-soft); could have even more to offer now returned to 3m although his participation could depend on how much rain arrives.

column4: Kildress Plumbing Chase (Grade 2)
column20: 5/6 Firefox, 11/4 Gorgeous Tom, 5/1 Croke Park, 13/2 Speculatrix, 66/1 Rockstown Girl, 150/1 Ivar The Boneless
column36: Smart novice form last year, below best on return at Punchestown, Kennedy deserts
column37: One of three for yard; started last season with three wins, including Grade 1 novice chases at Fairyhouse (Firefox and Gorgeous Tom behind) and Leopardstown; beaten 5l by Ballyburn at the DRF in February before failing to fire at Aintree; below best on seasonal return at Punchestown; carries a penalty here and Kennedy jumps ship.

column4: Kildress Plumbing Chase (Grade 2)
column20: 5/6 Firefox, 11/4 Gorgeous Tom, 5/1 Croke Park, 13/2 Speculatrix, 66/1 Rockstown Girl, 150/1 Ivar The Boneless
column36: Grade 3 win at Cork last season, solid Gr 1 runs in defeat after, go well if rain misses
column37: Won a Grade 3 novice at Cork last year and flew home when beaten just 1l in fourth behind Croke Park and Firefox in the Drinmore; ran well enough in defeat when fourth in Grade 1 novice at Cheltenham; not as good at Punchestown in April; can go well if ready to rock on seasonal reappearance but wouldn't want too much rain.

column4: Kildress Plumbing Chase (Grade 2)
column20: 5/6 Firefox, 11/4 Gorgeous Tom, 5/1 Croke Park, 13/2 Speculatrix, 66/1 Rockstown Girl, 150/1 Ivar The Boneless
column36: Smart hurdler, good run in Gr 1 when last seen in April, soft fine, 2-2 at this track
column37: One of three for yard and preferred by Kennedy; smart over hurdles (rated 151) and has achieved the same rating over fences; beaten 4.5l in a Fairyhouse Grade 1 novice when last seen in April (2m4f, sft-hvy); 2-2 at this track (bumper and C&D beginners' chase) and forecast rain not an inconvenience; leading chance.

column4: Kildress Plumbing Chase (Grade 2)
column20: 5/6 Firefox, 11/4 Gorgeous Tom, 5/1 Croke Park, 13/2 Speculatrix, 66/1 Rockstown Girl, 150/1 Ivar The Boneless
column36: 0-15 and rated 82 over fences, out of his depth in this company
column37: Fifteen race maiden and rated just 82 over fences; out of his depth in this company.

column4: Kildress Plumbing Chase (Grade 2)
column20: 5/6 Firefox, 11/4 Gorgeous Tom, 5/1 Croke Park, 13/2 Speculatrix, 66/1 Rockstown Girl, 150/1 Ivar The Boneless
column36: Beaten by a 108-rated rival in a Cork novice latest, this looks too demanding
column37: Bumper and dual hurdle winner; beaten by a 108-rated rival when runner up in a Cork novice chase on latest; this looks too demanding.

column4: Kildress Plumbing Chase (Grade 2)
column20: 5/6 Firefox, 11/4 Gorgeous Tom, 5/1 Croke Park, 13/2 Speculatrix, 66/1 Rockstown Girl, 150/1 Ivar The Boneless

column4: Eventsec (Pro/Am) INH Flat Race
column20: 6/4 With Nolimit, 9/4 Ballyfad, 9/2 Chichester Park, 10/1 Stone Cold, 12/1 Lexington Wood, 14/1 Dubhain, 25/1 Paymelater, 28/1 Pedro The Poet, 66/1 Wild Ridge
column36: Bought for E175,000 after point win in April, market can guide as to expectations
column37: Tirwanako gelding purchased for E175,000 after a 4l Fairyhouse point-to-point win (yielding) in April; that form isn't the easiest to assess but he clearly has ability and the market can guide as to expectations on Rules' debut.

column4: Eventsec (Pro/Am) INH Flat Race
column20: 6/4 With Nolimit, 9/4 Ballyfad, 9/2 Chichester Park, 10/1 Stone Cold, 12/1 Lexington Wood, 14/1 Dubhain, 25/1 Paymelater, 28/1 Pedro The Poet, 66/1 Wild Ridge
column36: Form of maiden hurdle run at Listowel boosted, Derek O'Connor 3-11 for yard in bumpers
column37: Point-to-point winner made a very pleasing start under Rules' in a Listowel maiden hurdle last month (2m, gd-yld), beaten just 4.25l into third at 50-1 and the runner up has since franked the form; interesting in first bumper with Derek O'Connor an eye-catching booking (3-11 for yard in NHF races).

column4: Eventsec (Pro/Am) INH Flat Race
column20: 6/4 With Nolimit, 9/4 Ballyfad, 9/2 Chichester Park, 10/1 Stone Cold, 12/1 Lexington Wood, 14/1 Dubhain, 25/1 Paymelater, 28/1 Pedro The Poet, 66/1 Wild Ridge
column36: Loughanmore point winner in April, yard's runners respected here, check market
column37: One of two for yard; won a Loughanmore point-to-point in April (3m, gd-yld); the 0.5l runner up has since finished well beaten in a Punchestown bumper but yard's bumper runners always respected here so he's worth a market check.

column4: Eventsec (Pro/Am) INH Flat Race
column20: 6/4 With Nolimit, 9/4 Ballyfad, 9/2 Chichester Park, 10/1 Stone Cold, 12/1 Lexington Wood, 14/1 Dubhain, 25/1 Paymelater, 28/1 Pedro The Poet, 66/1 Wild Ridge
column27: S C E A Bertwood Stables & Mme Hermine De Soultrait
column36: Both starts at Punchestown, respectable fourth there latest, needs to improve further
column37: Both starts have come at Punchestown on yielding and good to yielding; beaten 19.5l when seventh on debut; 12l behind Davy Crockett when fourth there in June; needs to improve again to take this.

column4: Eventsec (Pro/Am) INH Flat Race
column20: 6/4 With Nolimit, 9/4 Ballyfad, 9/2 Chichester Park, 10/1 Stone Cold, 12/1 Lexington Wood, 14/1 Dubhain, 25/1 Paymelater, 28/1 Pedro The Poet, 66/1 Wild Ridge
column36: 0-8 in bumpers, 3rd at Bellewstown in July, below that level since, forecast rain a worry
column37: Doesn't lack for experience having run eight times in bumpers; best effort this year a 12.5l third at Bellewstown (2m1f, good) in July; below that level in three runs since and the forecast rain is not in his favour.

column4: Eventsec (Pro/Am) INH Flat Race
column20: 6/4 With Nolimit, 9/4 Ballyfad, 9/2 Chichester Park, 10/1 Stone Cold, 12/1 Lexington Wood, 14/1 Dubhain, 25/1 Paymelater, 28/1 Pedro The Poet, 66/1 Wild Ridge
column36: Poet's Word gelding, dam unraced, tongue tied for debut and best watched
column37: Poet's Word gelding was a E3,500 yearling; unraced dam closely related to 1m Group 1 winner Aqlaam, out of unraced half-sister to top-class Flat stayer Persian Punch; tongue tied for debut and best watched.

column4: Eventsec (Pro/Am) INH Flat Race
column20: 6/4 With Nolimit, 9/4 Ballyfad, 9/2 Chichester Park, 10/1 Stone Cold, 12/1 Lexington Wood, 14/1 Dubhain, 25/1 Paymelater, 28/1 Pedro The Poet, 66/1 Wild Ridge

column4: Eventsec (Pro/Am) INH Flat Race
column20: 6/4 With Nolimit, 9/4 Ballyfad, 9/2 Chichester Park, 10/1 Stone Cold, 12/1 Lexington Wood, 14/1 Dubhain, 25/1 Paymelater, 28/1 Pedro The Poet, 66/1 Wild Ridge
column36: Heavy defeat and pulled up in both maiden hurdle starts, hard to make a case for
column37: Heavy defeat and pulled up in maiden hurdles at Navan and Sligo 691 days apart; hard to make a case for.

column4: Eventsec (Pro/Am) INH Flat Race
column20: 6/4 With Nolimit, 9/4 Ballyfad, 9/2 Chichester Park, 10/1 Stone Cold, 12/1 Lexington Wood, 14/1 Dubhain, 25/1 Paymelater, 28/1 Pedro The Poet, 66/1 Wild Ridge
column36: Bought for 250,000GBP after point win, stoutly bred, market can reveal expectations
column37: One of two for yard; hacked up in a Liscarroll point to point (3m, yielding) in March and bought for 250,000GBP at the Aintree sales in April; dam closely related to Welsh National winner Le Beau Bai so will probably want further than this in time but the market can guide in relation to his stablemate.
